dumb luck is going to run out.

226
00:13:19,791 --> 00:13:22,583
But you've earned the right
to keep this one.

227
00:13:22,666 --> 00:13:23,625
[gasps]

228
00:13:23,708 --> 00:13:25,291
Master?

229
00:13:30,541 --> 00:13:32,958
[stammering]

230
00:13:35,916 --> 00:13:39,083
[ZED]
I wasn't told about this.

231
00:13:40,541 --> 00:13:42,166
[LEO]
Hey, are you ok?

232
00:13:42,250 --> 00:13:45,375
[STARPHASE] A one-two punch
of exhaustion and shock.

233
00:13:45,458 --> 00:13:46,916
I feel for the guy.

234
00:14:01,291 --> 00:14:03,750
[FEMT] All your plans and
that was just a coincidence?

235
00:14:03,833 --> 00:14:06,208
I told you, yes.

236
00:14:06,291 --> 00:14:08,666
There's not really any
point in lying about it.

237
00:14:08,750 --> 00:14:10,000
[ALIGURA humming]

238
00:14:10,083 --> 00:14:13,375
[FEMT] Except for the
fact that you are a liar.

239
00:14:15,083 --> 00:14:16,291
[munching]

240
00:14:16,375 --> 00:14:17,791
[KING OF DESPAIR]
Think what you wanna think,

241
00:14:17,875 --> 00:14:19,416
but I haven't lied to you.

242
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:22,000
Or maybe I'm just not in the
mood to tell the truth tonight.

243
00:14:22,083 --> 00:14:24,583
You giant liar!

244
00:14:24,666 --> 00:14:26,083
[KING OF DESPAIR]
Look at this way.

245
00:14:26,166 --> 00:14:28,666
Does it really matter if I had
anything to do with that?

246
00:14:28,750 --> 00:14:30,833
It happened and
that's what counts.

247
00:14:30,916 --> 00:14:33,875
I'm not gonna try to tell you it
was on purpose or an accident,

248
00:14:33,958 --> 00:14:36,250
but you can be damn
sure if it serves me,

249
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:38,208
I'm gonna hop on board.

250
00:14:38,291 --> 00:14:40,250
That make sense, or not?

251
00:14:41,833 --> 00:14:43,750
You wanna hop on
board something?

252
00:14:43,833 --> 00:14:48,125
I've got a nice big ride
for you right here.

253
00:14:48,208 --> 00:14:50,375
[KING OF DESPAIR]
Aligula! [laughs]

254
00:14:50,458 --> 00:14:51,708
[ALIGURA]
Ugh!

255
00:14:51,791 --> 00:14:55,041
I honestly thought it was
impossible, you maniac!

256
00:14:55,125 --> 00:14:56,833
[ALIGURA] Just don't think
they're gonna come cheap.

257
00:14:56,916 --> 00:14:59,083
[KING OF DESPAIR] Hey,
they're worth every penny!

258
00:15:01,125 --> 00:15:02,666
[ALIGURA]
It's your head if they break.

259
00:15:02,750 --> 00:15:05,166
[KING OF DESPAIR]
Yeah, yeah. Thank you so much!

260
00:15:06,583 --> 00:15:08,208
They're exactly what I need.

261
00:15:09,583 --> 00:15:11,208
[heavy breathing]

262
00:15:21,125 --> 00:15:22,583
[WHITE]
Black!

263
00:15:22,666 --> 00:15:24,291
Over here!

264
00:15:25,500 --> 00:15:26,875
[BLACK]
White.

265
00:15:28,208 --> 00:15:29,708
White!

266
00:15:29,791 --> 00:15:32,250
Stay back! It's not safe here!

267
00:15:37,791 --> 00:15:40,500
I'll let you have
my stupid body!

268
00:15:40,583 --> 00:15:43,666
But please, please,
leave my sister alone!

269
00:15:47,916 --> 00:15:49,958
I'm begging you, okay?

270
00:15:52,500 --> 00:15:54,166
But that's the only way!

271
00:15:54,250 --> 00:15:56,250
If you need hands.

272
00:15:56,333 --> 00:15:58,958
If you have to take,

273
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:01,000
then take what
you need from me!

274
00:16:18,666 --> 00:16:20,125
[WHITE]
William?

275
00:16:25,625 --> 00:16:27,541
[sinister laughter]

276
00:16:31,666 --> 00:16:32,916
Nope.

277
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:34,583
My name is [no audio].

278
00:16:37,916 --> 00:16:40,750
I'm sure we can help
each other out,

279
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:42,333
eh, sister?

280
00:16:47,041 --> 00:16:49,500
[whistling]

281
00:16:51,333 --> 00:16:53,000
Huh?

282
00:16:53,083 --> 00:16:54,875
Is that you, Black?

283
00:17:14,375 --> 00:17:17,291
I'm gonna need you to get
your friend's eyeballs for me.

284
00:17:19,333 --> 00:17:20,875
You do that,

285
00:17:20,958 --> 00:17:22,708
and I'll give you
your brother back.

286
00:17:24,250 --> 00:17:26,500
That is the deal
we made, after all.

287
00:17:29,875 --> 00:17:31,875
[WHITE]
But Leo's such a nice guy.

288
00:17:31,958 --> 00:17:33,708
[KING OF DESPAIR]
Yep.

289
00:17:33,791 --> 00:17:35,791
[WHITE]
He's got a little sister, too.

290
00:17:35,875 --> 00:17:38,375
[KING OF DESPAIR]
I'm aware.

291
00:17:38,458 --> 00:17:40,791
[WHITE]
It reminds me of us.

292
00:17:40,875 --> 00:17:42,458
[KING OF DESPAIR]
Yeah, I suppose.

293
00:17:43,958 --> 00:17:45,333
[WHITE]
It's just that I...

294
00:17:46,958 --> 00:17:49,291
I don't wanna lose
Leo as my friend.

295
00:17:49,375 --> 00:17:51,166
Impossible.

296
00:17:51,250 --> 00:17:54,125
You've held it together
pretty good until now, sis.

297
00:17:54,208 --> 00:17:56,375
Don't get stupid on me.

298
00:17:56,458 --> 00:17:59,000
Get your head in the game before
your brother runs out of time.

299
00:17:59,083 --> 00:18:01,208
Don't act like you
don't know the stakes.

300
00:18:02,625 --> 00:18:04,666
We're all playing
on borrowed time,

301
00:18:04,750 --> 00:18:07,250
and the game is well underway.

302
00:18:07,333 --> 00:18:09,208
You're the player here, White,

303
00:18:09,291 --> 00:18:11,166
Me, I'm just the banker.

304
00:18:11,250 --> 00:18:13,416
And your brother,
he's the bid.

305
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:16,291
The bets are placed,

306
00:18:16,375 --> 00:18:18,166
the cards are dealt.

307
00:18:18,250 --> 00:18:21,416
So there's no backing out
until the game is over.

308
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:22,875
Not for any of us.

309
00:18:24,708 --> 00:18:26,750
Just say my name if
you don't believe me.

310
00:18:30,291 --> 00:18:33,416
--[snoring]
--[clock ticking]

311
00:18:40,750 --> 00:18:42,333
[KLAUS]
You're up early.

312
00:18:42,416 --> 00:18:44,708
Hi, Klaus.

313
00:18:44,791 --> 00:18:47,041
Or perhaps you were
never down to begin with.

314
00:18:47,125 --> 00:18:48,583
Yeah, sorry.

315
00:18:48,666 --> 00:18:50,083
Let me clean up
all this mess.

316
00:18:57,125 --> 00:18:59,083
[KLAUS]
Long-hand, huh?

317
00:18:59,166 --> 00:19:01,541
Are you writing
a letter to your sister?

318
00:19:01,625 --> 00:19:02,833
Yeah,

319
00:19:02,916 --> 00:19:04,708
but,

320
00:19:04,791 --> 00:19:06,750
I keep coming up blank.

321
00:19:08,958 --> 00:19:11,333
I wanna write, but that's
as far as I'm getting.

322
00:19:11,416 --> 00:19:13,625
So I keep staring at the paper.

323
00:19:22,041 --> 00:19:23,416
Oh, thanks.

324
00:19:31,666 --> 00:19:34,375
[KLAUS]
Hey, Leonardo.

325
00:19:34,458 --> 00:19:37,625
It wasn't just your eyes
we welcomed here.

326
00:19:37,708 --> 00:19:40,000
Not in the least.
You know that,

327
00:19:40,083 --> 00:19:41,625
now don't you?

328
00:19:46,875 --> 00:19:48,666
[BEN]
Black?

329
00:19:48,750 --> 00:19:49,791
You mean Will?

330
00:19:49,875 --> 00:19:50,791
[WHITE]
Uh-huh.

331
00:19:50,875 --> 00:19:52,083
[BEN]
How'd you think of that?

332
00:19:52,166 --> 00:19:53,625
[WHITE]
Duh, daddy!

333
00:19:53,708 --> 00:19:55,708
You're the one who said it!

334
00:19:55,791 --> 00:19:59,291
Will is like black sake
and I'm like white sake.

335
00:19:59,375 --> 00:20:01,375
[BEN]
Oh, yeah.

336
00:20:01,458 --> 00:20:05,000
You know that I was just
making an analogy, right?

337
00:20:05,083 --> 00:20:06,250
And I was kinda drunk.

338
00:20:06,333 --> 00:20:07,541
Yeah, I know.

339
00:20:07,625 --> 00:20:09,750
Anyway, I still think it's cool.

340
00:20:09,833 --> 00:20:10,916
Yeah?

341
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:13,083
Mom totally agrees
with me, too.

342
00:20:13,166 --> 00:20:14,541
Oh?

343
00:20:15,666 --> 00:20:17,041
Actually,

344
00:20:17,125 --> 00:20:18,458
you know what?

345
00:20:18,541 --> 00:20:20,541
I'm starting to see
how fitting it is.

346
00:20:20,625 --> 00:20:22,291
My two kids,

347
00:20:22,375 --> 00:20:23,791
Black and White.

348
00:20:25,333 --> 00:20:27,583
[WHITE] White and black are
like the complete opposite

349
00:20:27,666 --> 00:20:29,500
on the color spectrum, right?

350
00:20:29,583 --> 00:20:32,083
And that's exactly
how William and I are.

351
00:20:33,375 --> 00:20:34,291
[BEN]
That's right.

352
00:20:35,750 --> 00:20:38,000
But even so,

353
00:20:38,083 --> 00:20:39,625
from where I'm sitting,

354
00:20:39,708 --> 00:20:42,958
the two of you are more
alike than you might realize.

355
00:20:43,041 --> 00:20:44,000
Hmm?

356
00:20:48,583 --> 00:20:50,416
Well yeah, of course
we are, Dad.

357
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:52,291
We are twins.

358
00:20:52,375 --> 00:20:53,958
That you are, Mary.

359
00:20:54,041 --> 00:20:55,791
There's certainly
no denying that one.

360
00:21:04,916 --> 00:21:06,750
From here on out,

361
00:21:06,833 --> 00:21:08,708
I want you to keep
an eye on Will.

362
00:21:08,791 --> 00:21:12,041
If it ever looks like he's
about to make a mistake,

363
00:21:12,125 --> 00:21:14,291
you've gotta set him on
the right track, okay?

364
00:21:16,125 --> 00:21:17,916
[WHITE]
Shouldn't he look out for me?

365
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:19,333
[BEN]
You don't need it.

366
00:21:19,416 --> 00:21:21,541
[WHITE] What kind of mistakes
are you talking about?

367
00:21:21,625 --> 00:21:22,875
[BEN]
Uh, I guess if you ever see him

368
00:21:22,958 --> 00:21:26,666
about to hurt someone,
or maybe, an animal?

369
00:21:26,750 --> 00:21:28,250
[WHITE]
What? William?

370
00:21:28,333 --> 00:21:31,166
I think that's the craziest
thing you've ever said!

371
00:21:31,250 --> 00:21:33,458
[BEN] Yeah. No, I know
how crazy it sounds!

372
00:21:33,541 --> 00:21:34,750
[WHITE laughing]

373
00:21:34,833 --> 00:21:36,458
[BLACK]
Hey, White!

374
00:21:36,541 --> 00:21:39,083
Hey, what's up, Black?

375
00:21:39,166 --> 00:21:40,416
You wanna know something?

376
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:42,958
You are both
one and the same.

377
00:21:43,041 --> 00:21:44,375
--[WHITE] What's that?
--[BLACK laughs]

378
00:21:44,458 --> 00:21:45,708
[BEN]
A little wish.

379
00:21:45,791 --> 00:21:47,333
[laughs]

380
00:21:48,916 --> 00:21:51,541
[BEN] That you'll
always have each other,

381
00:21:51,625 --> 00:21:53,625
and that you'll always
keep each other happy.

382
00:21:59,541 --> 00:22:02,791
[crying]

383
00:22:02,875 --> 00:22:04,750
[WHITE]
Dad.

384
00:22:04,833 --> 00:22:07,250
Mom.

385
00:22:07,333 --> 00:22:09,416
[KING OF DESPAIR laughs]

386
00:24:07,958 --> 00:24:09,500
[ZED]
My name's Zed O'Brien.

387
00:24:09,583 --> 00:24:11,208
I'm Libra's newest
charity case.

388
00:24:11,291 --> 00:24:14,458
I wasn't exactly given
the most gentle introduction.

389
00:24:14,541 --> 00:24:16,833
And with only three episodes
left, I am a little anxious

390
00:24:16,916 --> 00:24:18,250
about what's to come,

391
00:24:18,333 --> 00:24:19,875
but I guess that's all
part of the training.

392
00:24:19,958 --> 00:24:21,708
I'm getting along
well with everyone,

393
00:24:21,791 --> 00:24:23,750
and they're weirdly nice to me.

394
00:24:23,833 --> 00:24:25,666
Excluding Zapp.

395
00:24:25,750 --> 00:24:27,750
Next time on
"Blood Blockade Battlefront,"

396
00:24:27,833 --> 00:24:29,916
Run! Lunch!
Run! To the end.

397
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:32,333
If it takes this much
effort just to get lunch,

398
00:24:32,416 --> 00:24:33,958
well, I guess it
shouldn't be so surprising

399
00:24:34,041 --> 00:24:36,333
that the rest of
life is so hard.

